Five Year Accident History
There has been no arsine, phosphine, chlorine, or hydrofluoric acid releases resulting in onsite or off-site injuries, deaths, or property damage, or in off-site environmental damage, evacuations, or sheltering in place.

Emergency Response Program
Alta Devices has well-established emergency procedures and an active Emergency Response Team (ERT) on site to ensure rapid and appropriate response to hazardous material emergencies, including response to emergencies related to the regulated substances covered by this RMP. The emergency response procedures are contained in the Emergency Response Plan, accessible at the site and maintained by the EHS Manager. The document describes response procedures for various emergency scenarios, including the mitigation of hazardous material releases, agency notification procedures in the event of a hazardous material release, and emergency equipment available at the site.

Planned Changes to Improve Safety
Based on the studies conducted during preparation of this RMP, the following adjustments are planned to ensure continued safe operations:
¿ The facility will perform an additional PHA after the finalization of design to ensure that all safety requirements detailed in the July 6, 2015 PHA have been implemented.
